Qualifications:
1. A master's degree in transportation engineering, mathematics, urban planning, architecture, landscape architecture, urban studies, or related physical and social science fields;
2. A baccalaureate degree in engineering from an accredited college and one year of full-time satisfactory experience performing technical work on roadway transportation and traffic studies and area-wide traffic programs;
3. A baccalaureate degree from an accredited college and two years of full-time satisfactory experience as described in '2' above;
4. An associate degree or completion of 60 semester credits from an accredited college and four years of full-time satisfactory experience as described in '2' above;
5. A four-year high school diploma or its educational equivalent and six years of full-time satisfactory experience as described in '2' above.
